  "limitations": [
    "This is one synthetic source identity, one synthetic target identity, four controlled states and one dated production run per state. It is not a population benchmark, provider leaderboard or generation success rate.",
    "Face detection and box overlap show that a detector returned a similarly located face. They do not measure identity fidelity, expression accuracy, attractiveness or perceived realism.",
    "Pixel differences show where target pixels changed. They do not establish whether an identity transfer is aesthetically correct.",
    "The four target states are purpose-built still images rather than independent photographs captured from natural motion.",
    "The production provider, queue and model behavior can change. A future run requires a new capture date and dataset version rather than silent replacement.",
    "Inspect the exact target and output files at full resolution before drawing a visual conclusion; this dataset intentionally publishes no universal quality score."
  ],
